# `.stow-local-ignore` (GNU Stow)

[`stow . --target="$HOME"`](mdc:.agents/setup-and-scripts.md) treats the repo root as a Stow **package**: every top-level file and directory can become a symlink under `$HOME` unless it is listed here. This file is **[`.stow-local-ignore`](mdc:.stow-local-ignore)** at the package root.

## What to include

Add **repo-only** top-level names that must **not** be deployed to `$HOME`:

- **Documentation and agents:** `doc`, `.agents`, [`AGENTS.md`](mdc:AGENTS.md), `README.md`, `LICENSE`
- **Tooling / package lists:** `scripts`, [`Brewfile`](mdc:Brewfile), [`.brewignore`](mdc:.brewignore)
- **VCS / editor / OS noise:** `.git`, `.gitignore`, `.cursor`, `.DS_Store`, `.gitkeep`

Do **not** list real dotfiles meant for the home tree (e.g. `.zshrc`, `.config`, `.zsh`, `.tmux.conf`)—those should be stowed.

Stow also **hard-ignores** [`.stow-local-ignore`](mdc:.stow-local-ignore) itself so it is not symlinked; you do not need to add that entry.

## How to enter values

GNU Stow parses this file as **Perl regular expressions**, one per line (see **Ignore Lists** in `info stow` or the [Stow manual](https://www.gnu.org/software/stow/manual/html_node/Ignore-Lists.html)).

| Input shape | Meaning |
|---------------|---------|
| **No `/` in the pattern** | Matched against the **whole basename** (one segment at the top level of the package). |
| **`/` in the pattern** | Treated as a **path** pattern (subpaths; use when you need to ignore a path that contains `/`). |
| **`#`** | Comment: empty lines and lines whose first non-whitespace character is `#` are skipped. Inline `#` after a pattern is stripped. |
| **`.` (dot)** | In regex, `.` matches **any** character. For a literal dot in a name (e.g. `.zshrc`, `AGENTS.md`), use **`\.`**. |

After edits, verify with a dry run (no writes):

```bash
rm -rf /tmp/stow-home-test && mkdir -p /tmp/stow-home-test
stow -n -v . --target=/tmp/stow-home-test
```

Only intended dotfiles and dirs (e.g. `.config`, `.zsh`, `.zshrc`) should appear under `LINK:`.

### Examples

```text
# ✅ Good: literal dots escaped; plain names need no escape unless regex-special
\.agents
\.cursor
\.gitignore
AGENTS\.md
README\.md
doc
scripts

# ❌ Bad: '.' matches any character; these are not reliable for ".agents" / "AGENTS.md"
.agents
AGENTS.md
```

